<Stem>
  <Paragraph>
   <Sentence>
     Let <italics>a</italics><sub>1</sub>, <italics>a</italics><sub>2</sub>, <italics>a</italics><sub>3</sub>,
	 <emphasis> ...</emphasis>, <italics>a</italics><sub><italics>n</italics></sub>, <emphasis> ...</emphasis>
	 be a sequence of positive numbers. 
     The first four terms of the sequence are given below.
     </Sentence></Paragraph>
   <Paragraph><Sentence><blockquote> 4, 12, 20, 28,<emphasis> ...</emphasis>
     </blockquote></Sentence></Paragraph>
  <Paragraph>
   <Sentence>
     Select the correct rule for finding the (<italics>n</italics>+1)th term from the <italics>n</italics>th term.
     </Sentence>
   </Paragraph>
  </Stem>

